descript.abstract: National Basketball Association (NBA) Arenas in the United States and Canada..
descript.supplinf: This dataset replaces original dataset compiled by NGA PMHP in January 2007.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.1850

attracc.attraccr: Various open sources (e.g. NBA team websites, Wikipedia) were utilized to update, where necessary, the following fields: Date Created, Date Modified, Names, Addresses, Latitude, Longitude, Comments, Conference, Division, Capacity, and Team.

dataqual.logic: See "Attribute_Accuracy_Report". Many of the checks described in that section check for both attribute accuracy and logical consistency.
dataqual.complete: This dataset consists of all National Basketball Association Arenas located in either the United States or Canada.

horizpa.horizpar: The correct geographic location of each site was verified using high resolution open source imagery, coupled with other open source reference materials. Each point was placed directly atop the entity itself.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attr.attrdef: Feature geometry.
The conference in which the basketball teams plays. Eastern or Western.

enttyp.enttypd: This is a list of all the National Basketball Association (NBA) arenas located within the United States and Canada.

attr.attrdef: The name of the Homeland Security Infrastructure Program (HSIP) area of interest (133 Cities Urban Area) within which an asset is located.
Feature geometry.

Assets have been categorized by NGA Preparedness Branch analysts and assigned to a primary asset sector, using the HSIP Tiger Team Report, ver. 1.1, of September 2002 as a guideline for categorization.

Assets have been categorized by NGA Infrastructure Analysis Branch analysts and assigned to an asset subsector, as defined in the HSIP Tiger Team Report, and as modified/expanded by Preparedness Branch analysts to accommodate the given assets.
The primary organization in charge of the basketball team operating at this site.
The date, in YYYYMMDD format, when a record was created for the NBA arenas.
The date, in YYYYMMDD format, when a record was last evaluated, and when accuracy and attribute changes were made, where necessary.
The company affiliation of a site, when known, to show the relationship of a subsidiary to a parent company.
This is the primary accepted name of the site.
The secondary name of a site, if available. Can be an unofficial name commonly used for the site.
The tertiary name of a site, if available. Can be an unofficial name commonly used for the site.
The street address at which a site is physically located, or a street corner at which a site is located.
The second line for a street address, used to indicate a specific building, or a suite number, a room number, or a floor.
The Post Office box for a site, if known.
The 5- or 9-digit Zip Code for a site, if known and if different than the Zip Code for the physical address of the site.
The city or town in which the site is located.
The two letter postal identifier for the state, commonwealth, or territory in which the site is located.
The Zip Code for the site. Principally, this Zip Code is for where the site is physically located, although there exist some exceptions.
The Zip+4 for the site, if known, provided, or researched.
The county, parish, or independent city name in which a site is located.
The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) region in which a site is located.
The latitude, in decimal degrees, of a site, to 5 decimal places.
The longitude, in decimal degrees, of a site, to 5 decimal places. Negative numbers in this field are for those locations in the Western Hemisphere.

This rating (High, Medium, or Low) by Infrastructure Analysis analysts is an estimate of the reliability of the geocoordinates. Ratings are non-quantitative, but rather respectively represent whether the analyst believes the geocoordinates to be within a city block of the site's rooftop, to be within a kilometer of the site's rooftop, or to be beyond a kilometer of the actual physical site. In the case of assets that have been geocoded by NGA, a Medium reliablity is generally assigned. Where analysts have gone in and performed additional refinements to the geospatial location, using high res commercial imagery, a HIGH reliability is assigned.
The division within the league the basketball team plays in. Atlantic, Central or Southeast (Eastern) or Southwest, Pacific or Northwest(Western).

The primary source used to determine a site's geocoordinates, although several sources may have been used to cross-check a location or street address. These other sources include maps, Web search sites, address geocoding functions, and customer-provided addresses and coordinates.
This field is used for comments about the asset, in terms of name changes, ownership, pending sales, status/decommissioning, location, or certain details about activities at that asset.
The seating capacity of the arena for basketball.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.
